    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="688"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 25010/36.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Italian Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Italian Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Manchester, Mass.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1229.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: Referring to previous
                    communications, and in accordance with the provisions of Article V of the
                    extradition convention of March 23, 1868, I have the honor to lay before your
                    excellency a formal request for the extradition of Porter Charlton, who has
                    confessed the crime of murder committed on the person of his own wife at
                    Moltrasio, Como, which crime is specified in Article II, section 1, of the said
                    convention.</p>
                <pb facs="0765" n="653" xml:id="pg_653"/>
                <p>Your excellency has already been so good as to forward to me in note No. 864, of
                    June 28 last, the preliminary certificate of arrest provided by Article II of
                    the additional convention of June 11, 1884, with a view to the provisional
                    arrest of the above-named accused.</p>
                <p>In support of this request I have the honor to transmit herewith to your
                    excellency the record of proceedings conducted by the court of Como in the case
                    of the aforesaid murder. The papers are regularly viséed by the embassy of the
                    United States at Rome.</p>
                <p>Awaiting the Federal “warrant” and the kind return of the inclosed papers for
                    submission to the competent court,</p>
                <p>I avail, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Montagliari.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
